      <trans-unit id="10182" identifier="040d4678ba6a3ab98c3ef3f88be72e83">
        <source>To find out if a number is even or odd, use the &lt;code&gt;scratch:() mod ()&lt;/code&gt; block
(under &quot;Operators&quot;) to find the remainder after dividing that number by
two.</source>
        <target>crwdns10182:0crwdne10182:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10183" identifier="ddf7560290ec7be5a041a73a4b5832fb">
        <source>If the remainder is zero the number is even.</source>
        <target>crwdns10183:0crwdne10183:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10184" identifier="7459f2da4f299b192c2ef9c89777d4bf">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:(37) mod (10) //7&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10184:0crwdne10184:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
